Very good weeknight dish. I did add some chicken broth to prevent dryness but other than that stuck to the recipe. I've made a recipe similar to this one in the past, but I really liked the inclusion of pine nuts in this one. I will definitely make this again.

Rating: 3
I recipe was good with a little tweaking. I followed the suggestion from other cooks to double the sauce amount and by doing so it was perfect for 3/4lb linguine pasta. I added about 1/4 cup white wine to the shallots after they sauted. I allowed the wine to come to a boil then added the cream and allowed the mixture to boil again. The rest was made as stated. It turned out very nice and I will not hesitate to make this recipe again, as it is a quick, easy and tasty main course for dinner.

